What the hell do you guys want?

295
00:16:44,641 --> 00:16:49,073
Well, we're having a problem
with the signal from camera two again.

296
00:16:57,873 --> 00:17:00,479
Hey! FBI!
Drop the gun!

297
00:17:07,163 --> 00:17:08,663
Special Agent Hagen?

298
00:17:09,909 --> 00:17:11,792
It's me. McSweeten.

299
00:17:12,008 --> 00:17:14,427
Todd, from the Moscone
mob case last year?

300
00:17:14,428 --> 00:17:16,389
Oh.
Yeah!

301
00:17:17,619 --> 00:17:19,645
- I lost--
- You dropped this.

302
00:17:21,044 --> 00:17:22,034
Yeah.

303
00:17:22,353 --> 00:17:24,787
I- I didn't even realize.
Yes, I dropped it.

304
00:17:24,788 --> 00:17:28,695
- Agent Thomas, good to see you again.
- Right back at you. Um...

305
00:17:28,959 --> 00:17:31,688
- Taggert from the Moscone case.
- R- right.

306
00:17:32,289 --> 00:17:35,313
Right. Right. So, uh,
what you all been up to?

307
00:17:35,397 --> 00:17:38,653
Well, actually, we've had
a pretty good run of it lately.

308
00:17:38,654 --> 00:17:40,287
- Closed some big cases.
- Big.

309
00:17:40,288 --> 00:17:42,938
- Moscone, for one.
- Moscone, no more-ne.

310
00:17:42,939 --> 00:17:45,480
We also shut down
a huge meth ring in California...

311
00:17:45,481 --> 00:17:47,255
during a bank robbery.

312
00:17:47,414 --> 00:17:49,725
What are you guys doing here?

313
00:17:50,075 --> 00:17:52,929
I mean, we--
We're undercover, man.

314
00:17:53,107 --> 00:17:56,375
Yeah, yeah. More manpower
on the Fowler case.

315
00:17:56,548 --> 00:17:58,961
- Oh, well, we never have been notified--
- They never said anything about--

316
00:17:58,962 --> 00:18:00,712
We're your secret backup.

317
00:18:01,254 --> 00:18:03,451
- Well... that's great!
- Hey! That's good.

318
00:18:03,452 --> 00:18:05,320
Shh! Secret!

319
00:18:07,374 --> 00:18:10,651
So, me and you--
You, I-- us--

320
00:18:10,652 --> 00:18:13,187
We should resume surveillance.

321
00:18:13,290 --> 00:18:14,323
Fellas.

322
00:18:18,173 --> 00:18:21,140
Can you imagine having
her for a partner?

323
00:18:23,009 --> 00:18:24,014
What?

324
00:18:24,410 --> 00:18:27,950
- You want to see other partners?
- I didn't say that.

325
00:18:28,099 --> 00:18:30,175
- Yeah. Fine. Whatever.
- That's not what I meant!

326
00:18:30,176 --> 00:18:33,250
Let me just g- get this straight,
okay. All right, you two--

327
00:18:33,251 --> 00:18:35,815
You couldn't rig a gym class
or a spelling bee?

328
00:18:35,825 --> 00:18:39,694
And you two-- you run into the only FBI
agents on the planet that recognize you?

329
00:18:39,695 --> 00:18:43,048
I got to be honest with you.
I think we broke the kid even more.

330
00:18:43,049 --> 00:18:45,956
We are the worst
fairy godparents in the world.

331
00:18:45,957 --> 00:18:50,215
Uh, listen, we still got to get Fowler
out of the apartment so we can get in.

332
00:18:50,216 --> 00:18:52,966
Yeah, except now when he leaves,
there will be somebody waiting to kill him.

333
00:18:52,967 --> 00:18:56,717
One of his victims wants payback
more than he wants to be paid...

334
00:18:56,885 --> 00:18:57,735
Back.

335
00:18:57,736 --> 00:18:59,923
One of you two can identify
the gunman, right?

336
00:18:59,924 --> 00:19:03,116
Oh, yeah, sure. He stopped and let me take
a picture of him as I was chasing him.

337
00:19:03,117 --> 00:19:06,185
Hey, you know what, man? I've been around little
kids all day. I don't need to come home...

338
00:19:06,186 --> 00:19:08,157
- and do all this crap.
- Hey, man, with all that?

339
00:19:08,158 --> 00:19:11,151
I've been in this pink shirt and these
tight plaid pants, these old webster loafers...

340
00:19:11,152 --> 00:19:13,188
This girl is walking on my back.
I don't need this, man.

341
00:19:13,189 --> 00:19:14,914
Is this the guy?

342
00:19:15,580 --> 00:19:16,745
See?

343
00:19:18,800 --> 00:19:21,392
Wow. I didn't know you could do that.

344
00:19:21,570 --> 00:19:23,820
I thought everybody could do that.

345
00:19:24,297 --> 00:19:27,141
Okay. All right, all right.
We'll keep an eye on him.

346
00:19:27,142 --> 00:19:31,035
In the meantime, if they think
you're real FBI, be real FBI.

347
00:19:31,036 --> 00:19:33,138
I mean, use it to case the apartment.

348
00:19:33,139 --> 00:19:37,013
All right, so I'm out of this, and I'm
on FBI detail with Parker and Hardison.

349
00:19:37,014 --> 00:19:39,249
Actually, no.
I need you to be coach Brewer, so...

350
00:19:39,250 --> 00:19:43,889
There's an armed gunman out there. You want me
in the gym with kids named Skyler and Indigo?

351
00:19:43,890 --> 00:19:45,991
Where did coach Brewer go?

352
00:19:45,992 --> 00:19:49,622
- I mean we are... there
- Shh! Shut up! Shut up!

353
00:19:52,708 --> 00:19:57,407
"The play is the thing where in
I'll catch the conscience of a king."

354
00:19:57,408 --> 00:19:59,201
* ...times I'm up *

355
00:19:59,399 --> 00:20:02,028
* Sometimes I'm down *

356
00:20:02,485 --> 00:20:05,672
* Ohh, Lord *

357
00:20:06,217 --> 00:20:10,245
* Sometimes I'm almost to the ground *

358
00:20:10,246 --> 00:20:13,496
Sophie, how long would it take
you to stage a musical?

359
00:20:13,616 --> 00:20:15,016
Six weeks.

360
00:20:15,270 --> 00:20:16,983
You have two days.

361
00:20:19,566 --> 00:20:24,295
* There can be no confusion
that fusion powers the star *

362
00:20:24,755 --> 00:20:25,854
D- did...

363
00:20:26,930 --> 00:20:30,066
- Did you just make that up on the spot?
- Yes, ma'am.

364
00:20:30,067 --> 00:20:34,308
- Huh. You really are quite relentless.
- Thank you, ma'am.

365
00:20:34,532 --> 00:20:36,208
M- Miss Donovan?

366
00:20:37,119 --> 00:20:39,775
Why are we singing
at a science fair?

367
00:20:39,776 --> 00:20:42,170
Ah. Good point, yes.

368
00:20:42,654 --> 00:20:45,274
Science. Knowledge.

369
00:20:45,640 --> 00:20:48,412
What is knowledge
without emotional context?

370
00:20:48,413 --> 00:20:50,731
- Facts.
- Uh-uh. Empty. Meaningless.

371
00:20:50,732 --> 00:20:53,032
We're taking left brain--
Science--

372
00:20:53,033 --> 00:20:55,814
And combing it with right brain--
creativity--

373
00:20:55,815 --> 00:20:58,698
To engage the audience's entire brain.

374
00:20:58,699 --> 00:21:03,851
Now, just- just present your projects,
and we'll just set it to a little melody.

375
00:21:04,015 --> 00:21:05,011
Who's next?

376
00:21:05,012 --> 00:21:07,614
* I can make a battery out of a potato *

377
00:21:07,615 --> 00:21:08,867
Thank you.

378
00:21:08,868 --> 00:21:12,428
- But I can turn on a light bulb.
- Mnh-mnh. That won't be necessary.

379
00:21:12,429 --> 00:21:13,840
Mr. Fowler?

380
00:21:14,390 --> 00:21:17,999
* You might find this distasteful *

381
00:21:18,081 --> 00:21:20,560
* Or call it just plain gross *

382
00:21:21,114 --> 00:21:24,942
* To sing in praise
of bread mold or wonder *

383
00:21:25,177 --> 00:21:26,519
* How it grows *

384
00:21:26,650 --> 00:21:29,544
* It even makes you crazy *

385
00:21:29,750 --> 00:21:33,329
* That mold devours your food *

386
00:21:37,631 --> 00:21:39,683
I don't know what to say, Widmark.

387
00:21:39,684 --> 00:21:42,298
- I- I'm sorry.
- No, no, no. That was...

388
00:21:42,382 --> 00:21:45,007
That was--
Yes, that was impressive.

389
00:21:45,008 --> 00:21:49,322
It was-- It was understated.
It was-- It was potentially wonderful.

390
00:21:49,433 --> 00:21:50,344
Yes!

391
00:21:50,522 --> 00:21:55,225
You, Widmark, are gonna sing
in the grand finale.

392
00:21:55,423 --> 00:21:58,173
Security system installed,
5- camera set-up.

393
00:21:58,174 --> 00:22:02,412
Two in the living room,
entryway, hallway, kitchen.

394
00:22:02,911 --> 00:22:05,420
Could I take a look at your logs
for Fowler's phone calls?

395
00:22:05,421 --> 00:22:08,856
I- I mean, if I put in a request
to home office-- It takes forever.

396
00:22:08,857 --> 00:22:11,831
Pencil pushers don't understand
what it's like for us out in the field...

397
00:22:11,832 --> 00:22:14,755
- face-to-face with crime.
- Yeah, nose-to-nose with evil.

398
00:22:14,756 --> 00:22:16,333
I can hear that.

399
00:22:16,746 --> 00:22:18,875
The files are in here.

400
00:22:27,579 --> 00:22:30,122
- Who the hell are you?
- FBI.

401
00:22:30,766 --> 00:22:35,081
There are cameras everywhere.
You people don't need to be in here.

402
00:22:44,736 --> 00:22:48,893
Out of every kid in the entire school,
she picks him for the showcase performance?

403
00:22:48,894 --> 00:22:51,482
- D- does she even know who he is?
- A student who--

404
00:22:51,483 --> 00:22:54,258
Whose father ripped off
everyone in this school.

405
00:22:54,259 --> 00:22:57,955
I'm a money manager. I put millions
of my client's accounts with him.

406
00:22:57,956 --> 00:23:01,729
We lost everything. And there isn't a parent
in this school who doesn't have the same story.

407
00:23:01,730 --> 00:23:04,644
Ja, it's not our philosophy
to punish the kinder...

408
00:23:04,645 --> 00:23:07,849
for the sins of their parents,
Mr. Sanford.

409
00:23:07,952 --> 00:23:12,160
And Ms. Donovan, she assures me
that Widmark's starring role in the, uh...

410
00:23:12,161 --> 00:23:13,487
The science-sical.

411
00:23:13,488 --> 00:23:16,865
Ja, science-sical--
Is, uh, based solely on merit.

412
00:23:16,866 --> 00:23:20,490
Now, if you excuse me, I have
a lot of work to do, please.

413
00:23:20,762 --> 00:23:23,212
Good afternoon.
Nice to see you again.

414
00:23:23,360 --> 00:23:26,723
Goodbye. Goodbye.
Goodbye, goodbye.

415
00:23:30,346 --> 00:23:33,345
Could you just please try to
maybe not make this so difficult?

416
00:23:33,346 --> 00:23:37,117
I can't take you seriously
with that dead cat on your head.

417
00:23:40,351 --> 00:23:42,490
Eliot had trouble adjusting, all right?

418
00:23:42,491 --> 00:23:46,291
But he found a way to make his style
work in this setting, so...

419
00:23:48,310 --> 00:23:50,619
Hai! Pain! Honor! Strength!

420
00:23:54,432 --> 00:23:55,624
All right.

421
00:23:57,192 --> 00:23:58,561
Come at me!

422
00:24:01,985 --> 00:24:04,641
It was the best I could manage
under such short notice.

423
00:24:04,642 --> 00:24:07,455
The props are made, the kids have
memorized their presentations.

424
00:24:07,456 --> 00:24:09,820
- I'm just setting it to a bit of music.
- Listen. We-- I mean...

425
00:24:09,821 --> 00:24:12,321
let's not forget why we're here.
Let's not lose focus.

426
00:24:12,322 --> 00:24:15,760
I mean, the object is to get Fowler
out of the apartment, not--

427
00:24:15,761 --> 00:24:18,417
What? Not-- not Widmark.
Right, yeah, I get it.

428
00:24:18,418 --> 00:24:20,627
- He's just the bait.
- Come on. That's not fair.

429
00:24:20,628 --> 00:24:23,819
What's not fair is the way people see him.
His father sees him as a loser...

430
00:24:23,820 --> 00:24:26,770
his mother sees him
as this fragile little baby...

431
00:24:26,854 --> 00:24:29,930
his schoolmates see him as the boy
whose father stole Christmas.

432
00:24:29,931 --> 00:24:32,746
I just think he--
He-- he...

433
00:24:33,826 --> 00:24:34,636
Ohh.

434
00:24:37,227 --> 00:24:40,429
I just want people to see him
as he really is.

435
00:24:41,105 --> 00:24:43,053
He deserves that.

436
00:24:44,643 --> 00:24:46,226
Everybody does.

437
00:24:57,035 --> 00:24:59,542
This is why we can't have nice things.

438
00:24:59,626 --> 00:25:01,934
Rich guys and their crazy
security systems.

439
00:25:01,935 --> 00:25:05,932
Door alarm's got a Takashita 500
with redundant infrared.

440
00:25:06,177 --> 00:25:08,412
- Window's easier.
- The window?

441
00:25:08,413 --> 00:25:12,254
- The window that's 20 stories up?
- Like I said-- easier.

442
00:25:12,618 --> 00:25:17,719
I've done this a million times. All I need
is a pneumatic drill, some diamond bits--

443
00:25:17,861 --> 00:25:19,420
Go, go, go.

444
00:25:22,477 --> 00:25:23,322
Hey.

445
00:25:25,500 --> 00:25:26,346
Hey.

446
00:25:26,609 --> 00:25:29,179
- Oh, uh, thanks.
- What's up?

447
00:25:29,180 --> 00:25:32,300
Oh, that one's actually mine.

448
00:25:33,746 --> 00:25:36,272
Uh, I just had my lips on that.
If.. uh...

449
00:25:36,273 --> 00:25:39,259
It's like I gave you
a little coffee kiss.

450
00:25:39,794 --> 00:25:42,234
I think your partner is sweet
on McSweeten.

451
00:25:42,235 --> 00:25:44,294
- What? No.
- I dont really talk about this kind of stuff.

452
00:25:44,295 --> 00:25:46,404
No? Well anyway.

453
00:25:46,504 --> 00:25:49,218
Uh, the judge approved
Fowler's day pass...

454
00:25:49,349 --> 00:25:52,107
so he can go see some play
his kid is doing at school.

455
00:25:52,108 --> 00:25:54,257
Final-freaking-ly, man!

456
00:25:54,679 --> 00:25:58,250
I- I love the theater.
It's-- "Cats".

457
00:25:58,390 --> 00:25:59,837
R- reow!

458
00:26:00,081 --> 00:26:03,074
All right, well, see you downstairs
in a couple of minutes.

459
00:26:03,075 --> 00:26:05,214
- Um, what?
- You're our backup.

460
00:26:05,215 --> 00:26:08,573
- You're coming along with, right?
- Yeah. Yeah.

461
00:26:08,574 --> 00:26:11,659
- You got our back, right?
- We, we, we-- Jo, yeah.

462
00:26:11,669 --> 00:26:15,253
- We got your back.
- Okay. Good.

463
00:26:18,718 --> 00:26:20,884
Nate, we got a problem...

464
00:26:20,885 --> 00:26:22,640
- Straight in that way.
- Well, so do we.

465
00:26:22,650 --> 00:26:26,200
It's final rehearsal, and so far
Widmark hasn't sung a note.

466
00:26:26,497 --> 00:26:28,197
* You *

467
00:26:30,374 --> 00:26:31,942
- Shh!
- Hey!

468
00:26:35,744 --> 00:26:38,636
The camera's charged, right?
I don't want to miss a second.

469
00:26:38,637 --> 00:26:41,476
Sir, I'm gonna have to check that bag.

470
00:26:42,312 --> 00:26:45,760
Oh, uh, hey, guys,
can we get a minute?

471
00:26:47,400 --> 00:26:49,296
Look, uh, quick update.

472
00:26:49,306 --> 00:26:52,351
One of us is gonna have to stay upstairs
